                  </persName>
            . I am parish clerk of St. Martin in the Fields. I produce the register of marriages, by which I find 
               <persName id="t18210214-126-person1283">
                  John 
                  Peat
               <interp inst="t18210214-126-person1283" type="surname" value="Peat"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210214-126-person1283" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210214-126-person1283" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was married to 
               <persName id="t18210214-126-person1284">
                  Mary 
                  Bond
               <interp inst="t18210214-126-person1284" type="surname" value="Bond"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210214-126-person1284" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210214-126-person1284" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , on the 18th of August, 1799. It is signed by both parties, and witnessed by 
               <persName id="t18210214-126-person1285">
                  William 
                  Goldborough
               <interp inst="t18210214-126-person1285" type="surname" value="Goldborough"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210214-126-person1285" type="given" value="William"></interp>
